ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBearClaw = Singular Bear Claw
    .desc = A massive golden claw from a bear of near-mythical proportions. The surface shimmers with an iridescent sheen, and the tip is sharp enough to puncture reinforced body armor. Stalkers speak of golden bears that guard the hearts of anomaly fields. This claw alone is worth more than most expeditions yield in a month.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBearEye = Singular Bear Eye
    .desc = A magenta-burning eye from a psi-bear of legendary psychic power. Even preserved, it induces vivid dreams in anyone who sleeps near it. The crystalline structures within the lens appear to store and amplify psionic energy indefinitely. Scientists theorize this eye alone could power experimental psionic equipment. Truly one of a kind.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBearPaw = Singular Bear Paw
    .desc = An enormous golden paw from a legendary Zone bear. The sheer mass of this appendage defies biological norms. The claws are embedded with crystalline formations identical to artifact matter, and the pad radiates faint warmth even hours after harvest. The Ecologists consider specimens like this the key to understanding the Zone's endgame.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBlindDogTail = Singular Blind Dog Tail
    .desc = A blood-red tail pulsing with residual warmth, taken from a blind dog of terrifying proportions. Stalkers whisper of crimson pack leaders that hunt near the edges of anomaly clusters where reality itself bends. The tissue contains crystalline microstructures that faintly resonate when near artifacts. Priceless to any collector.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBloodsuckerTentacles = Singular Bloodsucker Tentacles
    .desc = Golden-tinged tentacles from a bloodsucker of almost supernatural power. The tissue radiates warmth and faintly glows in darkness. Stalkers who have survived encounters with such creatures describe an overwhelming psychic pressure — as if the beast could sense their fear. These tentacles contain trace amounts of artifact-grade compounds. The scientific community would wage war over this specimen.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryBoarHoof = Singular Boar Hoof
    .desc = An enormous hoof radiating faint warmth, taken from a boar of near-mythical proportions. Stalkers who have seen such creatures claim they dwell near the center of anomaly fields where no ordinary beast could survive. The tissue contains trace amounts of an unidentified substance with properties resembling raw artifact matter. The Ecologists would pay a fortune for this.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryCatGland = Singular Cat Gland
    .desc = An extraordinary gland from a bayun of legendary power. The organ is crystalline in structure and radiates a warmth that numbs the mind of anyone holding it too long. The chemical cocktail within defies analysis with standard equipment. Only the most well-funded research stations could afford to acquire this, and they would pay handsomely for the privilege.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryFleshEye = Singular Flesh Eye
    .desc = An enormous golden eye radiating faint warmth, harvested from a flesh mutant of mythical proportions. The lens contains microscopic artifact-like formations that refract light in impossible patterns. Stalkers who have seen such creatures claim they glow faintly in the dark. The Ecologists would kill for this specimen.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryFrogLeg = Singular Frog Leg
    .desc = An extraordinary leg from a seer of terrifying size. The limb is covered in iridescent scales that shift color with temperature, and the muscles within contain a compound that Ecologists have never seen before. Rumors say the creature this came from could leap across entire anomaly fields in a single bound. A specimen of incalculable research value.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryIzlomArm = Singular Izlom's Arm
    .desc = A terrifying arm from an izlom of immense power and intelligence. The limb is armored in bony plates that have fused into a natural exoskeleton, and the hand has developed an additional joint that grants it a crushing grip strength beyond measurement. Veterans who have seen the creature this came from say it moved with deliberate purpose, almost human. A specimen that haunts the dreams of those who study it.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryLeshiyRoot = Singular Leshiy's Root
    .desc = An awe-inspiring root from a leshiy of immense age and power. The root is as hard as steel yet flexible, and it hums with an energy that makes nearby vegetation visibly grow faster. Stalkers who have carried one report vivid dreams of ancient forests. This is the kind of specimen that could fund an entire research expedition.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryOldBoarHoof = Singular Old Boar Hoof
    .desc = An immense amber-gold hoof from an old boar of legendary proportions. The surface shimmers with an opalescent sheen, and the tissue contains trace amounts of an unknown crystalline compound identical to artifact matter. Stalkers speak of this creature as a force of nature. The Ecologists would empty their coffers for this.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryOraculeEye = Singular Oracle Eye
    .desc = A mesmerizing eye from an oracle of staggering proportions. The organ is the size of a human head and appears to contain an entire miniature galaxy of bioluminescent organisms within its fluid. Staring into it too long induces hallucinations of places the viewer has never been. This is the kind of specimen that redefines what Ecologists thought possible about Zone mutations.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryPseudodogTail = Singular Pseudodog Tail
    .desc = A crimson-red tail radiating palpable heat from a pseudodog of terrifying power. Stalkers who have encountered such beasts report reality distortions in their wake — phantom images that persist long after the creature has gone. The psionic energy saturating this tissue is unlike anything documented. Worth more than most artifacts.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryPseudogiantHeart = Singular Pseudogiant Heart
    .desc = The heart of a pseudogiant of legendary proportions. The organ is nearly the size of a man's torso and radiates heat like a furnace. Each beat, which continues days after extraction, sends tremors through the ground. The tissue is saturated with an unknown energy that causes nearby anomalies to fluctuate. No price tag can capture the true value of this specimen to Zone researchers.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryPsiDogTail = Singular Psi-Dog Tail
    .desc = A magenta-glowing tail from a psi-dog of almost mythical psychic potency. Even severed, it causes vivid hallucinations in anyone who holds it for too long. Stalkers claim these creatures can drive entire squads mad from a hundred meters away. The psionic energy contained in this specimen exceeds anything measured in controlled laboratory conditions. Handle with extreme caution.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendarySeasonedBoarHoof = Singular Seasoned Boar Hoof
    .desc = A massive, fiery-orange hoof from a seasoned boar of near-mythical size. The surface is covered in hairline fractures that glow faintly with residual thermal energy. Veterans of the Zone claim these beasts charge through active anomaly fields unscathed. Worth a small fortune to the right buyer.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendarySnorkFoot = Singular Snork Foot
    .desc = A dark crimson foot from a snork of terrifying size and power. The claws have hardened into something resembling polished obsidian, and the muscle tissue is saturated with an unknown compound that grants impossible strength. Veterans of the Zone speak of these creatures in hushed tones — the ones that hunt in silence and strike from nowhere.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartLegendaryZombieHand = Singular Zombie Hand
    .desc = A hand from an ancient zombie of terrifying resilience. The limb is almost petrified, harder than stone, yet it still twitches occasionally when touched. The tissue emits a faint psionic field that disturbs sensitive equipment. Researchers would give anything to study this specimen, one of the rarest examples of sustained Zone mutation on formerly human tissue.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBearClaw = Mutated Bear Claw
    .desc = A silver-grey claw from a bear whose coloring has shifted through prolonged anomaly exposure. The internal structure has become partially metallic — X-ray analysis reveals a lattice of mineral deposits woven through the keratin. An incredible specimen of Zone-driven biomineralization.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBearEye = Mutated Bear Eye
    .desc = A teal-glowing eye from a psionically gifted bear whose mutation has reached an advanced stage. The pupil has expanded to fill nearly the entire iris, and the lens contains bioluminescent compounds that glow in darkness. Proximity causes mild psychic discomfort. An extremely rare find.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBearPaw = Mutated Bear Paw
    .desc = A silver-tinged paw from a bear that has undergone radical mutation. The bones have partially fused, creating a club-like structure of devastating striking power. The fur has taken on a metallic sheen that deflects low-caliber rounds. A remarkable specimen.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBlindDogTail = Mutated Blind Dog Tail
    .desc = A frost-pale tail from an albino blind dog — an extraordinarily rare mutation triggered by sustained exposure to gravitational anomalies. The vertebrae have partially fused into a rigid whip-like structure. Researchers at the Yantar lab consider these specimens critical for understanding Zone-driven neural evolution.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBloodsuckerTentacles = Mutated Bloodsucker Tentacles
    .desc = Ghostly white tentacles from an albino bloodsucker — a predator that has become one with the anomalous darkness. The bioluminescent cells along each tentacle pulse with a hypnotic rhythm. Scientists theorize this specimen could remain invisible even under direct observation. An extraordinarily dangerous trophy.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareBoarHoof = Mutated Boar Hoof
    .desc = A pale, almost translucent hoof from an albino boar — an extremely rare genetic drift caused by sustained anomaly exposure. The bone structure shows microscopic crystalline inclusions similar to artifact formations. Ecologists consider these specimens invaluable for understanding Zone-induced mutagenesis.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareCatGland = Mutated Cat Gland
    .desc = A grotesquely enlarged gland from a bayun whose psionic abilities have mutated far beyond the norm. The organ emits a low hum that makes nearby stalkers uneasy, and the concentrated chloral compounds within could sedate a pseudogiant. Researchers at the Ecologist camps would pay top roubles for this specimen.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareFleshEye = Mutated Flesh Eye
    .desc = A grotesque, purple-veined eye from a flesh mutant warped beyond recognition by concentrated anomaly exposure. The pupil has split into a compound structure resembling insect optics. Ecologists theorize this represents a radical evolutionary branch found only in the deepest anomaly fields.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareFrogLeg = Mutated Frog Leg
    .desc = A bone-white leg from a seer whose body has been fundamentally altered by prolonged anomaly exposure. The musculature is unlike anything found in nature, with fibers arranged in a helical pattern that grants extraordinary jumping power. Ecologists studying locomotion mutations consider these specimens invaluable.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareIzlomArm = Mutated Izlom's Arm
    .desc = A bone-white arm from an izlom that has undergone severe secondary mutation. The limb is nearly twice the length of a normal human arm and the joint structure has been completely rearranged, allowing impossible angles of rotation. The tissue is cool to the touch yet the muscles contract reflexively when stimulated. A deeply unsettling specimen that Ecologists find invaluable for their research.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareLeshiyRoot = Mutated Leshiy's Root
    .desc = A pale, almost translucent root from a leshiy that has absorbed massive quantities of anomalous radiation. The root pulses with an internal light and the sap within has crystallized into tiny formations that refract light like prisms. Ecologists theorize these specimens hold the key to understanding how the Zone transforms plant matter.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareOldBoarHoof = Mutated Old Boar Hoof
    .desc = A ghostly white hoof from an ancient boar bleached by years of gravitational anomaly exposure. The interior is hollow and resonates with a low hum when struck — the bone has been restructured into a natural acoustic chamber. Ecologists have never documented anything like it.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareOraculeEye = Mutated Oracle Eye
    .desc = An enormous, crystalline eye from an oracle that has undergone extreme mutation. The cornea has hardened into something resembling quartz and the multiple pupils have merged into an intricate fractal pattern. Some stalkers claim these eyes can still see, even severed from the creature. Research teams have been known to bid against each other for specimens like this.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRarePseudodogTail = Mutated Pseudodog Tail
    .desc = An electric-blue tail from a pseudodog whose fur crackles with residual static discharge. The creature appears to have developed a symbiotic relationship with electrical anomalies, channeling their energy through its nervous system. An extraordinary find for psionic researchers.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRarePseudogiantHeart = Mutated Pseudogiant Heart
    .desc = An impossibly dense heart from a pseudogiant whose cardiovascular system has mutated beyond recognition. The organ has a crystalline lattice structure woven through the muscle tissue, and it generates enough force to pump blood through a creature twice its already enormous size. Ecologists theorize this mutation could explain the creatures' near-invulnerability. Worth a fortune to the right buyer.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRarePsiDogTail = Mutated Psi-Dog Tail
    .desc = A spectral green tail from a psi-dog that has transcended typical psychic mutation. The tissue pulses with visible energy in dim light, and proximity causes mild headaches in unprotected humans. Scientists theorize the creature could project illusions across vast distances. An extremely dangerous specimen to handle.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareSeasonedBoarHoof = Mutated Seasoned Boar Hoof
    .desc = An ice-pale hoof from a seasoned boar whose pigmentation has been completely stripped by sustained chemical anomaly exposure. The bone structure has become semi-translucent, revealing an internal lattice of mineral deposits. Ecologists consider this among the finest examples of Zone-induced mineral accretion.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareSnorkFoot = Mutated Snork Foot
    .desc = A bone-pale foot from a snork whose skin has lost all pigmentation through extreme anomaly exposure. The joints have fused into a spring-loaded mechanism of terrifying efficiency. Ecologists note the bone density exceeds that of any known mammal — a testament to the Zone's power to reshape biology.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartRareZombieHand = Mutated Zombie Hand
    .desc = A ghostly pale hand from a zombie that has undergone secondary mutation. The bones have fused into a single solid structure and the tissue has been replaced by something that is neither flesh nor mineral. Ecologists are baffled by how the hand still functions and are willing to pay generously for study specimens.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBearClaw = Adapted Bear Claw
    .desc = A darkened, earth-stained claw from a bear that has roamed the deepest forests of the Zone. The keratin has hardened beyond normal biological limits, capable of scoring steel. Military collectors prize these as trophies of Zone survival.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBearEye = Adapted Bear Eye
    .desc = A dark, psionic-tinged eye from a Zone bear with heightened psychic sensitivity. The iris has developed unusual refractive properties, suggesting the creature could perceive psionic energy fields directly. Valuable to researchers studying Zone-born psychic phenomena.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBearPaw = Adapted Bear Paw
    .desc = A massive, calloused paw from a Zone-hardened bear. The pad has thickened into a leathery shield resistant to chemical burns and radiation. Evidence of years spent traversing the most hostile terrain the Zone has to offer.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBlindDogTail = Adapted Blind Dog Tail
    .desc = A thick, muscular tail from a blind dog that has survived longer than most in the Zone. The fur has coarsened into a bristly armor-like texture from prolonged radiation exposure. Ecologists note these specimens show accelerated nerve density — a sign of advanced Zone adaptation.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBloodsuckerTentacles = Adapted Bloodsucker Tentacles
    .desc = Dark, blood-crusted tentacles from a bloodsucker that has fed on Zone-contaminated prey for years. The suckers have developed barbed hooks for gripping armored targets. The tissue secretes a potent anticoagulant that researchers have been unable to synthesize artificially.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonBoarHoof = Adapted Boar Hoof
    .desc = A heavy, scarred hoof from a boar that survived many anomaly seasons in the Zone. The keratin has thickened from prolonged exposure to low-level radiation. Scientists at the Yantar mobile lab pay well for specimens showing signs of chronic Zone adaptation.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonCatGland = Adapted Cat Gland
    .desc = A swollen gland from a bayun that has adapted to the Zone's psionic fields. The tissue pulses with a faint bioluminescence, and the chemical compounds within are far more potent than the standard variety. Ecologists studying psionic mutations pay well for specimens like this.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonFleshEye = Adapted Flesh Eye
    .desc = A swollen, greenish eye from a flesh mutant that has fed extensively in anomaly-rich territories. The iris has developed an unusual bioluminescent sheen, suggesting the creature could perceive radiation spectra invisible to humans. Scientists pay a premium for specimens showing sensory adaptation.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonFrogLeg = Adapted Frog Leg
    .desc = A muscular leg from a seer that has adapted to the Zone's toxic marshes. The skin has developed a thick, leathery texture and the tendons are visibly reinforced. The meat within is denser than usual and carries a faint radioactive signature that Ecologists find fascinating.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonIzlomArm = Adapted Izlom's Arm
    .desc = A grotesquely elongated arm from an izlom that has adapted to the Zone's warping influence. The bones have stretched and thickened, and the muscles are corded with unnatural strength. The fingers end in hardened, claw-like tips that could tear through sheet metal. Researchers studying human mutation in the Zone will pay well for this.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonLeshiyRoot = Adapted Leshiy's Root
    .desc = A thick, gnarled root from a leshiy that has grown deep into the anomalous soil of the Zone. The bark-like surface is warm to the touch and seeps a sap that glows faintly green. Herbalists and Ecologists alike value this specimen for its unusual regenerative properties.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonOldBoarHoof = Adapted Old Boar Hoof
    .desc = A weathered, ash-grey hoof from an old boar that has endured decades in the deepest reaches of the Zone. The tissue has calcified into something closer to stone than keratin. Its very existence proves that some mutants don't just survive the Zone — they become part of it.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonOraculeEye = Adapted Oracle Eye
    .desc = A bulging eye from an oracle that has adapted to the deepest, most irradiated swamps of the Zone. The pupil has split into three, each one tracking independently, and the vitreous fluid within glows a sickly green. Ecologists studying mutant sensory evolution pay well for specimens of this quality.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonPseudodogTail = Adapted Pseudodog Tail
    .desc = A dark violet-tinged tail from a pseudodog that has hunted in anomaly corridors for years. The muscle fibers have become unusually dense, granting the creature explosive acceleration. Researchers note elevated psionic residue in the nerve tissue.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonPseudogiantHeart = Adapted Pseudogiant Heart
    .desc = A massive heart from a pseudogiant that has adapted to thrive in the Zone's most dangerous areas. The organ has developed additional chambers and the muscle walls are thick enough to stop a pistol round. The rhythmic contractions continue for hours after removal, a grim testament to the creature's vitality. Military researchers pay handsomely for these.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonPsiDogTail = Adapted Psi-Dog Tail
    .desc = A deep purple tail from a psi-dog whose psychic abilities have intensified through prolonged Zone exposure. The neural fibers running through the tail glow faintly under UV light, suggesting an expanded psionic nervous system. Valuable to researchers studying Zone-born telepathy.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonSeasonedBoarHoof = Adapted Seasoned Boar Hoof
    .desc = A battle-scarred hoof from a seasoned boar that has claimed territory deep within the Zone. The keratin shows layered growth rings from years of anomaly exposure, each ring denser than the last. Military collectors value these as proof of long-term Zone survival.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonSnorkFoot = Adapted Snork Foot
    .desc = A swamp-green foot from a snork that has adapted to the toxic marshes deep within the Zone. The tendons have thickened dramatically, granting the creature its legendary leaping ability. Military researchers pay well for specimens showing enhanced musculature.
    .suffix = Z14

ent-Z14STMutantPartUncommonZombieHand = Adapted Zombie Hand
    .desc = A hand from a zombified stalker that has survived far longer than most in its condition. The fingers have developed claw-like nails and the skin has hardened into a tough, bark-like surface. Military researchers are interested in the preserved nerve tissue, which still shows signs of electrical activity.
    .suffix = Z14
